A flat, intact, pigmented skin lesion that is 6 mm in diameter is most likely a macule, which is a small flat spot on the skin that is a different color than the surrounding skin. A papule is a raised, solid lesion, a plaque is a raised, flat lesion, and an ulcer is an open sore on the skin.
